Deaths from heart and blood vessel

"It's almost unbelievable.
There is almost no form of heart disease that we can't approach without meaningful treatment."
However, Weisfeldt, who is president-elect of the heart association, also cautioned that much work remains, both in improving care and encouraging people to take better care of their health.
Ischemic heart disease is the clogging of blood vessels that feed the heart.
It underlies most heart attacks, the single most lethal heart ailment.
Cancer, the No. 2 killer, took 466,000 lives.
_There were 1,418 heart transplants in 1987, almost nine times as many as in 1983.
_As many as 1.5 million Americans will have heart attacks this year.
